<br><h2 class=3D"title_grn">Definition: Poise</h2>
<p>The poise is a unit of dynamic viscosity in the CGS system of units. It =
is named after Jean Louis Marie Poiseuille. The analogous SI unit is the Pa=
scal second. Water has a viscosity of 0.0089 poise at 25 =C2=B0C, or 1 cent=
ipoise at 20 =C2=B0C.</p>


